rComments: Explains all concepts very well! Enthusiastic and keeps people focused on content even through the virtual learning! G.O.A.T
He is the best math prof ive ever met.

Seriously 4.5/5 !!! The prof is nice but he teaches math using only examples and R so you don't understand the theory. The rating is high simply because this teacher's exam is easy, but you will have a hard time in future courses.

Gilles Lamothe is an amazing teacher. He has the ability to explain complex concepts in a really simple way. He is very organized and patient, and always answers our questions (no matter how simple they are) without being rude. He truly cares about his students and wants them to succeed.

He is a very helpful and approachable professor, he is willing to answer student's question and explain things in details even after class. He also provide plenty of examples to help you understand the concept better. This is my first time learning Rmarkdown and I enjoy his class a lot, the things we learnt are super useful!

Gilles is a great professor. Do the suggested exercises, take notes in class, and start studying from the beginning of the semester. It is a big advantage to know how to use R, and R markdown. Gilles answers emails quickly and cares about his students. The course is very relevant and well organized.

Gilles is a great professor. He is always available to answer questions after class, answers emails quickly and cares about his students. One thing that stood out to me was his patience to answer low-level questions. He never was condescending no matter how poor the question. Do the practice problems and you'll be more than fine. Gilles is great!
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: He's one of the best professors of maths at uOttawa! His lectures are very clear, he's always responds to your emails lightning fast, always there for his students and does everything to help you succeed. Even though his TA sucks and the online final exam was pretty hard, he's a real gem and don't hesitate to take a class with him!

I took MAT 1373 but there's no option for this... Anyways he is a very good prof. If you are good at computer and math, you should take this class... While I am taking this class my laptop has a lot of problems so I always asked how to fix the problem after class. He always makes me feel comfortable even I couldn't catch the class.

Gilles is a great prof. He is able to explain concepts in a clear concise manner. He begins every lecture with a recap of the previous lecture to reinforce important concepts. Make sure to take notes, you'll need it for assessments. Strong computational skills in R is required to do well. It helps if you know LaTeX and RMarkdown as well.
Explained the subject material so well and his lectures were always interesting.
He is the best prof ever.

If you're a science study and not pure/minor math, please don't do not take this class as elective. Lamothe is an amazing person, but the content is not easy for non-math students. I gave him a good rating because he is great, but I had lots of difficulty understanding the material although I have 80 cgpa. Get textbook, got me through the course!

Good professor with really clear expectations, the midterm and final were really easy since the questions were practically straight out of the lectures. If you take the time to make good cheat sheets for the exams, it's an easy A.

One of the greatest profs ever! He's a real gem. What I liked most about his teaching style is that he does a small review from the day's past lecture when you start a new lecture. It really drills in the important concepts and refreshes you about things that you may need to look over. His assignments and midterm is quite easy- it's a great class!

Awesome guy, very very good teacher. Very clear examples and very good at explaining sometimes abstract concepts. Examples done in class and assignments are similar to exams and midterms. Would very highly recommend.
His textbook is awful. All examples, not general cases or abstract explanations.
Need go to class, do assignment. Almost every assignment will appear in midterm and final. This professor like to use R to solve Mathematical problems, so be prepare to use R .

One of the best math professor I've had, he really knows his subject and is very nice and caring. The class is very straightforward and he tells you everything that's gonna be on the exams. If you make your cheat sheet yourself it should be an easy A.

He was alright. Found his lectures to be confusing at times and it felt as though he wasn't always explaining things in order. Midterm was extremely easy, final was much more difficult. Make sure to look over your assignments because his TAs have no idea how to mark, they always miss marks.

Ses examens sont tellement raisonables; les exemples qu'il fait en classe te prepareront bien. En plus il est bin gentil et un vrai plaisir d'avoir pour un prof. cependant, il faut que tu ailles aux cours, car ses solutions sont pas mises sur brightspace.

I'm almost certain biostats class with this prof is the easiest course you can take in UOttawa, and I've taken Drugs 101 with Ogilvie. Explains concepts thoroughly, midterms and exam convey material covered in class to full extent, gave a bonus on final to account for mistake he made. He has a soft voice so if you go to class, sit near the front.

The first midterm was ridiculously easy (I got a 91.67% with only a day's worth of studying), but that set up the expectation that the final would be the same way as well. I, however, found his final to be much more difficult than his midterm. Sit up close to the board and actually do the assignments and you'll be ok. He's a sweet heart

To be honest, this is probably the easiest class I've taken up to this point. The midterm class MEDIAN was a 92. I'd imagine it was about the same for the final. The course content is jokes - I went to class maybe 5 times the whole semester and finished with an easy A+. Only downside was TAs who had no idea what they were doing for assignments.

Barely went to class. His midterm was the easiest midterm I've ever done at the University of Ottawa. His final was fairly easy too. The TAs are really picky on assignments but he's super reasonable if you go to his office hours. Would definitely recommend.
Most laid back prof ever! His TA's that mark the assignments suck though

Amazing prof! His lectures are very interesting and his grading criteria is clear. His examples are really useful for the midterm and the final. He is accessible outside class and takes time to answer all of your questions. Would to take again! By far my favorite prof!

He explains pretty well and will answer all your questions for the homework outside of class. This class is boring but pretty easy. If you write down the examples and do the homework, you'll get a decent mark.

Very good prof, he's super nice and is always ready to help his students outside of class. There are quite a lot of assignments but they are not worth a lot, considering the amount of work required. He often makes mistakes on his exercises and tests, so beware (he made 2 mistakes on our final exam).
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Accessible outside class', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Good lecturer, in terms of presenting the material in a clear and precise manner. He provides lots of examples during class along with the underlying concepts and theorems. Exams are fair and reflective of the material presented throughout the course. To succeed attend class, go over the examples show in class, do the assignments and practice!
Best prof ever!!! And i'm terrible in math. He tells you exactly what is on the midterm and final. You are allowed to have a cheat sheet. Easy A.

I hate maths + I am lazy af BUT I had an A+ !! This prof is WONDERFUL. He had a tremendous standing ovation on our last day of class. Yes, he's that good. His homeworks aren't too easy but his exams are!

Really, really good teacher! By far my favourite maths teacher. His explanations are clear and he gives useful tips. The only downside is that his exams are too long. I barely finished the midterm and I did not have time to finish the finals. Needless to say, it had an impact on my grade.

Il est un très bon professeur, explique bien et efficacement la matière. Il fait plusieurs exemples en classe, ce qui aide à bien comprendre la matière. 6 devoirs et 3 quiz sont à remettre, mais ils se font rapidement et c'est des points données. Cours relativement facile, je le recommande pour un cours au choix en science.

Feel like they made the class slightly harder than past years this year, midterm average was only a 67%. Gilles is a good prof but on the 2nd half of material (after the midterm) he stopped explaining things as well and the class was mainly just people asking questions on concepts because he wasn't clear enough. Book helps to explain things though.

Does multiple examples to really grasp the topic being discussed and does daily recaps of previous lecture before the start of class which is GREATLY appreciated. Don't be shy to e-mail him, he replies very fast. DO the online bank of questions and you're sure to pass with flying colours. Would recommend him for biostatistics!

Gilles Lamothe is an amazing professor!  Material was very dry but he is very clear in his explanations. No surprises on the midterms, they perfectly reflect the material and his practice midterms. Homework is somewhat harder than the tests but he only gives a few. All in all, read the notes, redo his examples and you'll get an A+!

Made maths very easy! The average on the midterm was about 80%, which says a lot. Always has the time to anwser questions. Also, he does multiple examples in class and they're useful for the homeworks.

Very clear about concepts and expectations, gives organized notes and loves to answer students' questions. Having a part mcq part short answer final was very helpful. Never felt like I was falling behind because of his mini-reviews at the beginning of class and the homeworks.
He's very nice and cares for his students. He's also very clear when he explains. His examples help alot, it's a relatively easy course
Very good prof! He made the class very easy. He's very clear and easy to understand. I would strongly recommend taking the class with him if you can.
He's really good at explaining complicated stuff and make it sound easy. A great prof
Amazing professor! Understand his notes and do all the practice questions and you're good. Answers emails really fast and is ready to help.

Mr. Lamothe is such a good teacher! His examples are very clear, his notes are very well organized and he always takes the time to answer your questions. The homeworks and exam are very easy, they reflect perfectly the class material, no surprises what so ever. I would definetly recommend this teacher!! :)
Great teacher! Course subject isn't the most interesting but he delivers it well and makes it slightly better.

Le meilleur prof que j'ai eu à date. Ces notes sont claires et précises mais il faut être au cours pour prendre en note les exemples. Ceux-ci sont très utiles pour les devoirs et vous aiderons énormément pour les examens. Il donne tous aux élèves pour qu'ils réussissent alors profitez-en.
Il est clair et explique très bien. Ses examens représentent bien les notes de cours. Il fournit beaucoup d'exercices afin d'être bien préparé aux examens.

Awesome prof, very clear expectations, excellent teaching and very useful study material. If you follow along, do the suggested problems the class will be interesting and easy.   Very fair midterm and final.
great prof.
He is always available to answer your questions in person or by email ans his lectures are very interesting! I would highly recommend his class.

Took Biostats with Gilles, fairly easy class, interesting prof, males learning stats easy. Multiple choice style exams, which sounds easy but fair warning, this is a math class so if you make a mistake in your math you will not get answer right at all, does even look at formula sheet, 5 home works somewhat easy, made to raise grade.

Super helpful prof. Conveys material very effectively and is very kind in answering questions he may have already answered earlier just the lecture. He sometimes makes super cute but cheesy jokes. Overall, love the prof and he helped me love a statistics course (who knew that was even possible) HIGHLY RECOMMENDED!
HE is indeed a great teacher and coveys the material perfectly.

Notes and expectations are super clear, assignments reflect the exams very well. Probably the most organized prof at UO. He gives you all the opportunities to get an A+; takes 4 of 5 assignments and tests you only on stuff from his notes. His textbook is also worth buying and reading (help you understand stuff better). Great guy, recommended!
helpful. easy. have to attend classes

Très passionné et clair avec sa matière. Statistics made easy with him. Faire les exercices recommendées et relire les notes et tout devrait relativement bien aller! Le format des examens est très plaisant!
Ce n'est pas le meilleur cours que j'ai pris, mais son enseignement a fait en sorte qu'il le devienne.

It isn't always easy to pay attention in class because it can get boring, but the homework and exams reflect the course material perfectly. He knows what he's talking about and is always willing to answer questions. Fantastic prof!
Amazing prof, he just makes sense, always availlable to help, midterm was fair, but surprising if not studied well. Just do the homework and extra excersices and you will have no problem!
Takes best 4 out of 5 marks for assignments, easy enough midterm, harder exam compared to practice one, really nice prof, good class overall

Excellent prof! Relaxed atmosphere. He makes the complicated so simple. Always available outside of class to answer questions in (just about) any math topic. Repeats the notions all the time, writes everything on the board. Very polite, very sociable, a real gentleman! Always asked us if we had questions. Easy HWs, harder exams. Listen to Gilles!

Excellent prof. Teaches well, always available for extra help, relates math to real life which makes you appreciate the usefulness of this subject. Make sure you go to class AND PAY ATTENTION cuz everything he says is important/helpfull. Do the homework properly and the questions online and an A+ is  (almost) garanteed.

Professeur très dédié à la réussite de ses étudiants. Il est toujours disponible pour répondre aux questions par e-mail ou en personne, et donne des notes de cours très claires. Ses devoirs sont longs parfois mais l'effort vaut la peine. Si tu comprends les devoirs, tu comprends la classe au complet! Meilleur prof de maths à date...!

Best math teacher I've ever had. Takes his time in class to make sure everything is understood. His notes are almost perfect. He's super nice and very helpful if you have questions. No surprises on exams or assignments. As a bonus to his awesome teaching, the class is almost as easy Calc I.
helpful prof! always available to answer questions. gives really good examples in class

Although it was his first time teaching the intro to Linear Algebra class he did a splendid job. Although the class itself is rather hard, he made everything as clear as he could. He's an generous marker, as well as always available to you for assistance. The only unfortunate part was we ran behind schedule a lot. But over all excellent prof!

Interesting lectures (for a statistics course), and the online course notes were great - very clear and easy to understand.  Open book exams (def make equations sheets, though, since you won't have time to be flipping through your books!).  All exams and midterms are multiple choice, and some of the questions are a bit confusing.
cool
favourite professor by far this year. He's easily the most straight forward and direct professor for math I've had to date. BRAVO

Good lectures, makes such good notes in class that you dont really need the textbook, but it helps alot with the assignments. do all the assignments well and get a good mark. Open book exams, but the exams are SO THICK that you dont have time to be flipping through your book.

had him wen he first started teaching n altho his classes are not entertaining he teaches material well good notes. he is also very helpful, even during MT. questions are straightforward n he allows a cheatsheet. Easy to talk u if u want more time, more cheat sheets...MT n final are super easy but u walk away not remembering a single thing :)
gilles is great--book totally useless, his notes are wonders tho
Good prof, teaches alright...IF you wanna do well in his class, do the assignments well.  AND...prepare your own notes!!!!  YOur notes will be very helpful for the exam and midterms.  Good luck

SUPER GREAT prof! assignments are very doable and lectures are very easy to follow. just a professor who really knows how to teach (unlike some other old bats who dont wanna retire and get the f*ck outa here)

Pathetically easy professor.Print out cheat sheets on computer; do all problems, get 90+ in the course.  His classes are so easy, you don't even think when solving problems...and hence, you learn nothing...just get a high mark.  Excellent lecturer though.

Nice guy.  Assignments & tests were great.  Unfortunately, no one can save prob & stats from being the math department's natural remedy for insomnia.
